   <body>
      <context/>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the panel in the bottom of the UPS.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS</title>
                  <image href="../Images/connect_power_cables_removebottompanel_0000066409.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the gland plates in the top of the AUX cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Realitypxc_general-topentryprepareforcables_w120mm_0000235801.svg"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Drill/punch holes for cables/conduits in the gland plates.
Install conduits (not provided), if applicable.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <hazardstatement type="danger">
                  <messagepanel>
                     <typeofhazard>Hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
                     <howtoavoid>Do not drill or punch holes for cables or conduits with
the gland plates installed and do not drill or punch holes in close
proximity to the cabinet.</howtoavoid>
                  </messagepanel>
               </hazardstatement>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reinstall the gland plates in the top of the AUX cabinet(s).</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Realitypxc_general-topentryprepareforcablesreinstall_w120mm_0000235800.svg"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
      </ol>
